          ],
          "logprobs": [],
          "text": "As of February 3, 2026, the SPDR Straits Times Index ETF (ES3.SI) had the following performance metrics:\n\n- **Year-to-Date (YTD) Return**: 5.39%\n- **1-Year Return**: 30.68%\n- **3-Year Return**: 19.94%\n\n([uk.finance.yahoo.com](https://uk.finance.yahoo.com/quote/ES3.SI/?utm_source=openai))\n\nOn February 4, 2026, the ETF announced a dividend distribution of SGD 0.085 per unit, comprising:\n\n- SGD 0.071 per unit from \"Singapore one-tier dividend and other exempt income\"\n- SGD 0.006 per unit from \"income taxable at Trustee level\"\n- SGD 0.008 per unit from \"other income\"\n\nThe ex-dividend date was set for February 11, 2026, with the record date on February 12, 2026, and payment scheduled for February 27, 2026. ([marketscreener.com](https://www.marketscreener.com/news/spdr-straits-times-index-etf-announces-dividend-distribution-payable-on-february-27-2026-ce7e5adadd89f421?utm_source=openai))\n\nAdditionally, on February 2, 2026, State Street Global Advisors Singapore Limited announced a rebranding of the ETF to \"State Street SPDR Straits Times Index ETF,\" effective March 3, 2026. This change affects only the fund's name and SGX labels, with no impact on its investment strategy, ticker symbol, portfolio management team, or investment objectives. ([links.sgx.com](https://links.sgx.com/1.0.0/corporate-announcements/B6D8GR3H0JGCPTQS/?utm_source=openai))\n\nAs of March 7, 2026, the ETF's net asset value (NAV) was SGD 5.0418, with a closing price of SGD 5.04 on February 4, 2026. ([poems.com.sg](https://www.poems.com.sg/etf-screener/sgx-es3/?utm_source=openai))\n\nPlease note that the ETF's performance and dividend distributions are subject to market conditions and may change over time. "
